# Incident Response Report

## Executive Summary
A simulated cyber attack exploiting a Samba vulnerability was conducted. The attack was detected, analyzed, and contained successfully.

## Timeline
- Attack executed using Metasploit
- Detection via logs
- Triage using TheHive
- Response using CrowdSec

## Root Cause
The system was vulnerable due to unpatched Samba service.

## Response Actions
- Case created in TheHive
- Tasks assigned
- Attacker IP blocked

## Metrics
- MTTD: 2 hours
- MTTR: 4 hours
- Dwell Time: 6 hours

## Recommendations
- Regular patching
- Better monitoring
- Automated response systems
